        q: 'What does The Devil mean in love?',
        a: `The Devil in love describes powerful attachment — the magnetic, often physical pull that binds two people in ways that can be intoxicating or quietly imprisoning. At its best, the card signals strong chemistry, deep sensuality, and a genuine appetite for one another. At its more difficult edge, it points to obsession, dependency, jealousy, or patterns that feel impossible to step out of. The card asks you to look honestly at which version you are inhabiting. Real intimacy includes the freedom to leave — and the chains in this card are looser than they appear. The pull is real; the helplessness is optional.`,
